The paper deals with privacy-preserving data publishing, which is a topic that falls under the database (cs.DB) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of wavelet transforms is a technique from information theory (cs.IT) that is applied to the data before adding noise to it. The paper also discusses the theoretical analysis of privacy and utility guarantees, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
